  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To evaluate the performance of LLMs in imperfect information environments that require collaboration, we selected Guandan foot_0, a popular Chinese card game.",
    "The game's objective is for two players on the same team to cooperate and play out all the cards in their hands as quickly as possible to achieve a higher team score (see Appendix A for detailed rules).",
    "In alignment with recent work, we evaluated commercial and Chinese open-source models without fine-tuning in a zero-shot setting against various agents, including the state-of-the-art RL agent Danzero+ (Zhao et al., 2023), to assess their adaptability and performance in an imperfect information environment requiring collaboration.",
    "Our evaluation found that LLMs performed poorly in this environment compared to Danzero+.",
    "To address this gap, we first analyzed the models' performance and discovered a significant need for LLM in handling variable and lengthy valid action lists."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In alignment with recent work, we evaluated commercial and Chinese open-source models without fine-tuning in a zero-shot setting against various agents, including the state-of-the-art RL agent Danzero+ (Zhao et al., 2023), to assess their adaptability and performance in an imperfect information environment requiring collaboration."
  ]
}